SCR 89 Original 2026 Regular Session Henry
Present rule provides that the following bills not be counted against the five-bill limit on bill
introductions after prefiling for the authors of those bills.
(1) The general appropriation bill.
(2) The bill appropriating funds for the judicial branch.
(3) The bill appropriating funds for the legislative branch.
(4) The capital outlay bill.
(5) The omnibus bond authorization bill.
(6) Appropriation bills supplementing the General Appropriation Act.
(7) The bill appropriating funds from the Revenue Sharing Fund pursuant to Article VII,
Section 26.
(8) The bill establishing and reestablishing agency ancillary funds.
Proposed rule retains this provision.
Proposed rule provides the following limits on the introduction of bills to be prefiled for
introduction in either house.
(1) No more than ten bills by any member who is not the chairman or vice chairman of
a standing committee.
(2) No more than twelve bills by any vice chairman of a standing committee.
(3) No more than fifteen bills by any chairman of a standing committee.
(4) If a member is both a chairman and vice chairman of a standing committee then the
fifteen bill limit for chairman applies.
Proposed rule prohibits a member from introducing more than ten resolutions, simple or
concurrent, that are not perfunctory. Provides that the following resolutions are not to be
counted against this ten-resolution limit:
(1) A resolution providing for the approval of a minimum foundation program formula
pursuant to Article VIII, Section 13 of the Louisiana Constitution.
(2) A resolution providing for a hospital stabilization formula pursuant to Article VII,
Section 10.13 of the Louisiana Constitution.
(3) A resolution providing for a master plan for integrated coastal protection or an
annual plan for integrated coastal protection pursuant to R.S. 49:214.5.3.
